Your `generateClass` class (BTW, by convention, Java class start with a capital, as in, `GenerateClass`) is missing the `map` variable.

Because your method is static, so must the variable be also. For example:

    public class GenerateClass {
        static final Map&lt;String,Object&gt; map = new HashMap();
 
        public static String getOrGenerateID() {
            if (map.containsKey(&quot;TestMapKey&quot;)) {   //check if map has a key
                return map.get(&quot;TestMapKey&quot;);     // return the value for the key
            }
        }
    }
    
----

If you make the `map` variable package-scoped, you can assign values in the test, to test. For example:

    public void getOrGenerateIDTest() {
        GenerateClass.map.put(&quot;TestMapKey&quot;, &quot;TestMapValue&quot;);
        String newID = GenerateClass.getOrGenerateID();
        Assertions.assertTrue(GenerateClass.map.containsKey(&quot;TestMapKey&quot;));
        Assertions.assertEquals(&quot;TestMapValue&quot;, map.get(&quot;TestMapKey&quot;);
    }

